---
import Card from '@mcp-orchestrator/design-system/components/Card.astro';
import Stack from '@mcp-orchestrator/design-system/components/Stack.astro';
import PageSection from './PageSection.astro';
---

<PageSection title="About Me">
  <Stack direction="vertical" size="md">
    <Card variant="default" size="md">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Background</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        I'm an AI/ML Initiative Lead and Enterprise Architect based in Muri bei
        Bern, Switzerland. With over 25 years of experience building large-scale
        distributed systems, I've worked at the intersection of software
        architecture, distributed computing, machine learning, and—most
        recently—agentic AI systems.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-3">
        Career Path
      </h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        My career has evolved across three distinct chapters:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm"
      >
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>Enterprise Architecture & AI Systems (2013–Present):</strong>
          Led architecture for SBB's omni-channel distribution, next-generation
          web presence (<a
            href="https://www.sbb.ch"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >sbb.ch</a
          >), and—most recently—agentic ecosystems using the <a
            href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >Model Context Protocol</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>Machine Learning & Document Analysis (2004–2011):</strong> Applied
          statistical learning (HMM, GMM, SVM) to handwriting recognition and writer
          identification, contributing to pattern recognition and document image analysis.
        </li>
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>Software Composition & Reengineering (2001–2003):</strong> Focused
          on formal methods (<a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi-calculus"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >π-calculus</a
          >), meta-modeling (MOF/XMI), and component-oriented programming at the
          <a
            href="https://www.unibe.ch/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >University of Bern</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-3">
        Current Focus
      </h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        I lead AI/ML initiatives at <a
          href="https://www.sbb.ch"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
          >SBB</a
        >'s Passenger Division, designing ecosystems of domain-expert agents
        coordinated via the <a
          href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
          >Model Context Protocol (MCP)</a
        >. My recent work explores formal verification of agentic systems,
        schema-driven interoperability, and scaling LLM-powered tools across
        large organizations.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-3">
        Education
      </h3>
      <ul
        class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm"
      >
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>PhD in Computer Science</strong> — <a
            href="https://www.unibe.ch/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >University of Bern</a
          >, 2008. Dissertation: "Writer Identification and Verification."
        </li>
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>Diplom (Master's)</strong> — <a
            href="https://www.unibe.ch/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >University of Bern</a
          >, 2002. Thesis: "Enabling White-Box Reuse in a Pure Composition
          Language" (<a
            href="https://scg.unibe.ch/research/piccola"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >JPiccola</a
          >).
        </li>
        <li class="pt-1">
          <strong>Bachelor's</strong> — <a
            href="https://www.unibe.ch/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
            >University of Bern</a
          >, 2001. Thesis: "Generic XMI Support for the MOOSE Reengineering
          Environment."
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-3">
        Open Source & Community
      </h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        I'm a long-standing contributor to open-source projects, including
        contributions to the <a
          href="https://kde.org/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
          >KDE HTML rendering engine (khtml)</a
        > and <a
          href="https://webkit.org/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
          >WebKit</a
        > CSS parser. I'm also the Technical Lead and Product Owner of the <a
          href="https://osdm.org/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors"
          >Open Sales and Distribution Model (OSDM)</a
        >, an international API standard for rail ticket distribution, now
        adopted by all major European railways and leading global distribution
        systems.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-3">
        Interests
      </h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        Beyond work, I'm fascinated by the intersection of formal methods and
        practical systems, the challenges of scaling machine learning in
        production, and the emerging paradigm of agentic AI. I believe the
        future of enterprise software lies in intelligent, schema-driven agent
        ecosystems that can dynamically compose tools across organizational and
        domain boundaries.
      </p>
    </Card>
  </Stack>
</PageSection>
